The UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Mae SCHEIBLE and Joe Ryan, Defendants-Appellants.* No. 167. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 2, 1936. Sanford H. Cohen, of New York City, for appellant Scheible. Edward W. McDonald, of New York City (George Cohen, of New .York City, on the brief), for appellant Ryan. Lamar Hardy, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Seymour M. Klein, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel; Robert L. Wernes, Sp. Asst, to U. S. Atty., of New York City, on the brief), for the United States.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

Writ of- certiorari denied 57 S. Ct. 329, 81 L. Ed. —.

 PER CURIAM.

Judgments affirmed.
